<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idef95dc2a-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idef95dc2b-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 105(a)(2)(B) of the Gulf of Mexico Energy Security Act of 2006, referred to in subsec. (b), is <ref href="/us/pl/109/432/dC/tI/s105/a/2/B">section 105(a)(2)(B) of title I of div. C of Pub. L. 109–432</ref>, which is set out in a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t43/s1331">section 1331 of Title 43</ref>, Public Lands.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idef95dc2c-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2019—<ref href="/us/pl/116/9">Pub. L. 116–9</ref> designated existing provisions as subsec. (a) and inserted heading, struck out “Not less than 40 percent of such appropriations shall be available for Federal purposes.” after “Fund.”, and added subsec. (b).</p>
</note>
